BEGIN:VEVENT
DESCRIPTION:Tickets $25\nPurchase Tickets\nA three-day fest with a dream lineup of avant-garde musicians in first-time collaborations.\n\nFor the first time since 2009\, the legendary\nNo Fun Fest\nreturns to New York with a three-day fest titled\nNo Fun New Perspectives\n\, focusing on improvised music and featuring a dream-like lineup of avant-garde musicians from different generations\, with every presentation during the festival a world premiere that will push experimental music to new and unknown places.\nNo Fun Fest was celebrated as a pivotal event in Experimental Music and Noise during its original run in New York City from 2004 to 2009\, and a second edition in Sweden in 2009.\nNIKA\n(prepared piano and voice) and\nNate Wooley\n(trumpet)\nZeena Parkins\n(harp)\,\nRyan Sawyer\n(percussion)\, and\nElaine Carey\n(electronics)\nMir Naqibul Islam\n(percussion) and\nRandall Dunn\n(electronics)\nMichael Vallera\n(guitar) and\nAlan Lich\nt (guitar)\nCarlos Giffoni\nis the person behind No Fun\, which included a festival that ran in NYC in different venues from 2004 to 2009\, multiple collaborations with other festivals around the world\, and the No Fun Productions label. Carlos is a Venezuelan musician who lived in the US from 1996 to 2025 and currently resides in Valencia\, Spain. With recent releases on Ideologic Organ and Room40. As well as recent residencies at GRM in Paris and EMS in Stockholm. He has collaborated with an impressive list of experimental musicians\, and his work has been featured in multiple fashion campaigns and films.
DURATION:PT2H
LOCATION:Roulette Intermedium\, 509 Atlantic Ave\, Brooklyn\, NY
DTSTART:20260712T000000Z
SUMMARY:No Fun New Perspectives: NIKA\, Nate Wooley\, Zeena Parkins\, Ryan Sawyer\, and more (Night 3)
UID:03680856-c59e-46da-9477-3661b19683aa@0368.org
URL:https://roulette.org/event/no-fun-new-perspectives-night-3/
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
DESCRIPTION:Tickets $35\nPurchase Tickets\nZorn's most powerful 21st century ensemble featuring longtime associates John Medeski\, Matt Hollenberg\, and Kenny Grohowski.\n\nFrom 2015–2022\, John Zorn composed and recorded a total of ten CDs of music for\nSimulacrum\n\, his most powerful and intense 21st century ensemble. Featuring longtime Zorn associates John Medeski (MMW\, Saudade\, Mad Skillet) on organ\, Matt Hollenberg (Shardik\, Titans to Tachyons\, Secret Chiefs 3) on guitar\, and Kenny Grohowski (Imperial Triumphant\, Titan to Tachyons) on drums\,\nSimulacrum\nis the most extreme organ trio ever.\nNo one blends metal and jazz quite like Zorn (Naked City\, Painkiller\, Moonchild\, Awakening Ground\, etc) and\nSimulacrum’s\nhyper-powered stop-on-a-dime live performances are legendary.\nThis rare appearance is their first NYC performance in over two years. Not to be missed!\nJohn Medeski\norgan\nMatt Hollenberg\nguitar\nKenny Grohowski\ndrums
DURATION:PT2H
LOCATION:Roulette Intermedium\, 509 Atlantic Ave\, Brooklyn\, NY
DTSTART:20260701T000000Z
SUMMARY:John Zorn’s Simulacrum
UID:50540e7f-2dbe-4512-a5b3-8c98e6f33119@5054.org
URL:https://roulette.org/event/john-zorns-simulacrum/
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
DESCRIPTION:Tickets $45\nPurchase Tickets\nZorn’s beloved ensemble w/ Julian Lage\, Jorge Roeder\, & Kenny Wollesen returns for the 5th consecutive year for one tight and telepathic set.\n\nThe New Masada Quartet—saxophone legend\nJohn Zorn\n’s beloved ensemble featuring guitar master\nJulian Lage\n\, bass wizard\nJorge Roeder\nand 30-year Zorn veteran\nKenny Wollesen\n—returns to Roulette for the fifth consecutive year!\nPerforming classic compositions from the Masada songbooks in one fiery set\, NMQ is a unit of like-minded virtuosi and one of the best groups Zorn has ever had. Led by Zorn’s versatile sax and stop and start conducting\, the music is filled with burning solos\, harmonious group interaction\, heartfelt lyricism\, and hypnotic grooves.\nJohn Zorn\nsax\nJulian Lage\nguitar\nJorge Roeder\nbass\nKenny Wollesen\ndrums
DURATION:PT2H
LOCATION:Roulette Intermedium\, 509 Atlantic Ave\, Brooklyn\, NY
DTSTART:20260616T000000Z
SUMMARY:RESCHEDULED – John Zorn: New Masada Quartet
UID:49cbfedf-1984-4bdd-8b2b-7941252e199c@49cb.org
URL:https://roulette.org/event/john-zorn-new-masada-quartet-2026/
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
DESCRIPTION:Tickets $25\nPurchase Tickets\nCommissioned artist shares new material\, fusing R&B/soul aural traditions and experiments in electronic music to explore new Black sonic forms.\n\nRoulette Commissioned Artist\nLambkin\nshares new material on vocals\, Ableton Push\, synthesizer\, FX pedal. Lambkin is a Brooklyn-based musician and composer. She fuses R&B/soul aural traditions and experiments in electronic music to explore new Black sonic forms.\n*FREE FOR ALL ROULETTE MEMBERS *\nA livestream will be available free of charge at 8pm on the day of the performance and archived for future viewing.\nLambkin\nis a DMV-born musician\, composer\, and director. Charged with a kinetic upbringing through rigorous dance training\, the Brooklyn-based artist attunes R&B/soul aural traditions and experiments in electronic music to the pulse of the heart\, head\, and body\, exhuming new Black sonic forms in the process.
DURATION:PT2H
LOCATION:Roulette Intermedium\, 509 Atlantic Ave\, Brooklyn\, NY
DTSTART:20260618T000000Z
SUMMARY:Lambkin
UID:8f91e8d6-fc56-460a-981f-8eb9e1d51324@8f91.org
URL:https://roulette.org/event/lambkin/
END:VEVENT
